Independence 
of judges and 
lawyers 
</p>
<p><b>Alleged arbitrary detention</b>. According to the information received, Mr. Ziad Wasef 
Ramadan was detained for over five years without any charge, trial or even being presented 
before a judge. He was to be presented before the State Security Supreme Court on 17 
January 2011. The Working Group on Arbitrary Detention considered, in its Opinion No. 
24/2010, that Mr. Ramadan's detention was arbitrary. Allegedly, Mr. Ramadan's lawyers were 
not been authorized to see him, and his family had only very brief contact with him.  
</p>
