Torture 
</p>
<p><b>Alleged arbitrary arrest, torture and harassment of a Christian human rights lawyer</b>. 
According to the information received, Dr. Fan Yafeng is a legal academic, human rights 
lawyer and a Christian church leader. On 30 October 2010, Dr. Yafeng was summoned by the 
authorities, and subsequently detained at the Shuangyushu hotel. On 7 November 2010, he 
was summoned and charged with disturbing the peace, following a gathering at the 
Shengshan Church. Dr. Yafeng was detained until 19 December 2010. During this time, he 
was allegedly taken to a hotel and hooded. Subsequently, he was taken to an unknown 
location where he was beaten and threatened by the guobao police. Under this pressure, Dr. 
Yafeng reportedly promised to abandon all his efforts in the context of human rights activism. 
</p>
