</p>
<p>Arbitrary 
detention;  
Independence 
of judges and 
lawyers;  
Torture 
</p>
<p><b>Alleged arbitrary detention of political activist</b>. According to the information received, on 
14 December 2010, Ms. Moshrefa Mishu, General Secretary of the Ganatantrik Biplobi Party 
and President of the Garment Workers Unity Forum was arrested by members of the Dhaka 
Metropolitan Police and detained in Dhaka Central Jail. Prior to her arrest, Ms. Mishu had 
reportedly received death threats from callers who introduced themselves as officers of 
intelligence agencies and the Special Branch of police. Ms. Mishu was reportedly interrogated 
about her visits abroad, the funders of her political activities, her relationship with external 
groups in China as well as her attachment with the workers&#8217; movements. The police 
reportedly insisted on her signing a blank piece of paper. Ms. Mishu refused, and was 
allegedly subjected to several death-threats by the police officers. The Metropolitan 
Magistrate reportedly rejected a bail petition, stating that he had strict direction from the 
Government not to grant bail to Ms. Mishu.  
</p>
