</p>
<p><b>Alleged killing of human rights defender and death threats against his family</b>. According 
to the information received, Mr. Sebasti&#227;o Bezerra de Silva was the coordinator of the west-
central branch of the National Human Rights Movement and a member of the Tocantins 
Human Rights Commission. Mr. de Silva was reportedly involved in investigating the use of 
extrajudicial executions, torture and other forms of ill-treatment by members of the Brazilian 
police force and security authorities. On 28 February 2011, the body of Mr. de Silva was 
reportedly discovered on a farm in the municipality of Duer&#233;, Tocantins State. An 
examination of the body reportedly revealed that Mr. de Silva had been subjected to torture 
before he was killed. In the period preceding his disappearance, Mr. de Silva and his family 
allegedly received numerous death threats via telephone.  
