</p>
<p>Afghanistan 
</p>
<p>Violence 
against women 
</p>
<p><b>Allegation that a proposed bill would regulate the operation of women&#8217;s shelters. 
</b></p>
<p>According to the information received, a draft regulation on women&#8217;s shelters undermines 
rather than upholds the protection provided by the Elimination of Violence against Women 
law. The acting Minister of Women&#8217;s Affairs had allegedly stated that the government had 
been determined to take control of all shelters, most of which had been run by NGOs. The 
proposed draft regulation allegedly creates barriers to admission into shelters, which could 
result in imminent threats to women trying to escape violence. 
</p>
