</p>
<p><b>Alleged threats and harassment against human rights defenders</b>. According to the 
information received, on 20 March 2011, Mr. Undule Mwakasungula, Executive Director of 
the Centre for Human Rights and Rehabilitation (CHRR), received death threats from 
unknown individuals. On 9 March, armed police officers visited Mr. Mwakasungula&#8217;s home 
in Karonga, allegedly claiming this was a routine check. Reportedly, on 3 March, a group of 
unidentified individuals broke into the CHRR offices in Lilongwe. These incidents reportedly 
form part of an ongoing campaign against human rights defenders in Malawi. On 14 
February, police in Lilongwe reportedly banned a peaceful march organised by civil society. 
Following the issuance of a statement condemning the recent wave of intimidation against 
them, the Human Rights Consultative Committee, a coalition of 90 organisations, reportedly 
received a letter signed by the National Youth Forum threatening to close down the coalition.  
</p>
