Torture 
</p>
<p><b>Alleged detention and ill-treatment of a lawyer and presidential candidate.</b> According to 
the information received, on 20 December 2010, Mr. Ales Mikhalevich, born 1975, was 
arrested by KGB officers who entered his flat by breaking the door and dragged him out by 
force. Mr. Mikhalevich was reportedly taken to the KGB detention centre in Minsk, where he 
was held until 19 February 2011. He claimed to have been subjected to ill-treatment and 
denied access to a lawyer. On 19 February he was reportedly charged with having incited 
mass riots in connection with demonstrations in Minsk on 19 December 2010. On the same 
day, he was reportedly released on bail and on the condition that he agreed to become a KGB 
informant. Fearing further persecution by the Belarusian authorities, Mr. Mikhalevich 
reportedly fled to the Czech Republic, where he sought political asylum.  
