Torture 
</p>
<p><b>Alleged arbitrary detention</b>. According to the information received, on 21 April 2011 Mr. 
Adbdullah Khowar, 29, a vendor, usually residing in Ain-Khaled, Doha, Qatar, was arrested 
by the security forces of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) at the border of Salwa when he was 
driving to the UAE. On the same day, Mr. Khowar was reportedly allowed to contact his wife 
and inform her that he was taken to the Damman prison in the UAE. He allegedly noted that 
he was not given any explanation for his arrest and that he feared for his safety. Reportedly, 
Mr. Khowar had expressed his political views in relation to the events taking place in the 
Middle East.  
</p>
