<p><b>Request to disclose facts in respect of the use of deadly force against Mr. Osama bin 
Laden</b>. According to information received, on 2 May 2011, the President of the United States 
of America, Mr. Barrack Obama, made a public statement that Mr. Osama bin Laden had 
been killed in Abbottabad, Pakistan, during an operation conducted by the United States 
Government. On 4 May, the United States Attorney General, Mr. Eric J. Holder Jr., indicated 
before the United States Senate that the killing of Mr. Osama bin Laden was lawful and was 
&#8220;justified as an act of national self-defense&#8221;. The exact details of the operation remained 
unclear; details emerging from Government officials remained sketchy and at times 
inconsistent. 
