Benedicto Kondowe, Executive Director of the Civil Society Coalition on Quality Basic 
Education. The men demanded that the security guard provide them with Mr. Kondowe&#8217;s 
home address and telephone number, which he refused to do. On 21 April, Mr. Kondowe 
reported the incident to the Area Three Police Station, Lilongwe. The same day, Mr. 
Kondowe reportedly received a threatening phone call from an unknown man. On 23 April, 
he reportedly received another phone call from an unidentified man who advised him to leave 
the country.  
