<p>IND 16/2010 
</p>
<p>India 
</p>
<p>Health; Torture <b>Alleged lack of access to palliative care and pain treatment. </b>According to the information 
received, more than half of India&#8217;s Regional Cancer Centres do not offer any palliative care 
for pain management. It is estimated that more than one million people suffer from moderate 
to severe pain due to advanced cancer, and only a few receive proper treatment. The same 
reportedly occurs for people with HIV/AIDS, paraplegics, patients with advanced renal 
diseases and others who require palliative care. Additionally, many of the Regional Cancer 
Centres do not have health workers who are trained in palliative care. 
</p>
<p>18/05/11 </p>

