<p><b>Alleged arrest of human rights defender</b>. According to information received, on 6 March 
2009 Ms. Chiranuch Premchaiporn, editor of Prachatai, an online media portal, was arrested 
for having allowed readers to post comments on Prachatai&#8217;s online discussion forum that 
allegedly defamed the King of Thailand. On 31 March 2010, she was reportedly arrested 
again for the same alleged offence. On 24 September, she was arrested again, at 
Suvarnabhumi airport in Bangkok upon returning from a trip to Lithuania and Hungary. She 
was allegedly shown an arrest warrant relating to material posted on the Prachatai website in 
April 2008. On 25 September 2010, Ms. Premchaiporn was released on bail, awaiting trial for 
the charges mentioned above, which in total could lead to a 50-year prison sentence.   
