<p><b>Alleged sale of children for forced labour in mines.</b> According to the information received, an 
estimated 70,000 bonded child labourers from Nepal and Bangladesh work at the so-called &#8220;rat 
mines&#8221; of Jaintia Hills, Meghalaya State, India. In most cases, the children are allegedly 
